SIMPLE: indestructible
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Indestructible
<hw>In`de*struc"ti*ble</hw>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Pref. <ets>in-</ets>
not + <ets>destructible</ets>: cf. F. <ets>indestructible</ets>.]</ety>
<def>Not destructible; incapable of decomposition or of being destroyed;
<as>as, the Russian harvesters had primitive electronics, but they were
built so sturdily they were almost <ex>indestructible</ex></as>.</def>
-- <wordforms><wf>In`de*struc"ti*ble*ness</wf>, <pos>n.</pos> --
<wf>In`de*struc"ti*bly</wf>, <pos>adv.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Indeterminable</ent>⟦br⟧
